104
00:05:55,695 --> 00:05:56,902
Most of the time, yes.

105
00:05:57,576 --> 00:06:00,470
But she can howl like a banshee when she wants something.

106
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:02,561
How long have you worked for Christine?

107
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:03,712
Oh, just a few months.

108
00:06:04,378 --> 00:06:06,202
The last nanny quit with no notice.

109
00:06:07,765 --> 00:06:09,543
Do you know why Christine is leaving town?

110
00:06:09,547 --> 00:06:11,522
She told me that she missed the city.

111
00:06:12,147 --> 00:06:14,741
You were right. So she can be closer to her office.

112
00:06:15,986 --> 00:06:19,032
Well, there are a lot of bad memories for her in this house.

113
00:06:20,425 --> 00:06:21,421
Painful memories.

114
00:06:25,848 --> 00:06:27,241
Uh, memories about her son?

115
00:06:28,336 --> 00:06:29,761
