Melinda, are you comfortable watching a baby?

264
00:15:22,758 --> 00:15:26,251
Hey, I bought a car off the baby-sitting money I made in high school.

265
00:15:27,328 --> 00:15:28,523
I guess that means yes.

266
00:15:29,165 --> 00:15:30,601
We'll take good care of her, ok?

267
00:15:30,615 --> 00:15:32,312
Just get home as soon as you can.

268
00:15:32,336 --> 00:15:35,231
Ok. Thank you so much, Melinda. Thank you for everything.

269
00:16:15,608 --> 00:16:16,751
Looking for something?

270
00:16:17,615 --> 00:16:18,612
I know you're here.

271
00:16:19,448 --> 00:16:20,342
Where is she?

272
00:16:20,717 --> 00:16:22,263
What did you do with the baby?

273
00:16:36,366 --> 00:16:38,062
You shouldn't have fallen asleep.

274
00:17:01,635 --> 00:17:02,532
Jim?

275
00:17:05,076 --> 00:17:06,170
Hello? Where are you?

276
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:08,880
Hey.

277
00:17:10,996 --> 00:17:12,291
Honey, I've been worried.

278
00:17:13,828 --> 00:17:14,723
Is everything ok?

279
00:17:14,865 --> 00:17:15,591
Yeah.

280
00:17:15,598 --> 00:17:16,610
Yeah, everything's good.

281
00:17:16,617 --> 00:17:18,962
I think spirit boy's messing with my head, but

282
00:17:19,108 --> 00:17:20,500
otherwise, things are fine.

283
00:17:20,635 --> 00:17:21,983
You're amazing to do this.

284
00:17:22,688 --> 00:17:23,681
It's like practice.

285
00:17:23,828 --> 00:17:25,023
Have you been sleeping?

286
00:17:25,456 --> 00:17:27,502
Yeah, she was up just a few minutes ago.

287
00:17:28,655 --> 00:17:30,342
You're wasting your time, Daniel.

288
00:17:35,835 --> 00:17:37,351
He was here. Now he's gone...

289
00:17:38,086 --> 00:17:38,983
for now.

290
00:17:41,027 --> 00:17:42,321
You think he's dangerous?

291
00:17:42,448 --> 00:17:44,103
If you can't see him, he might be.

292
00:17:44,116 --> 00:17:48,562
As long as I can keep an eye on him and not let Jessie out of my sight, we should be ok.

293
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:51,510
Christina will be on the first flight back in the morning.

294
00:17:52,828 --> 00:17:53,722
So, uh,

295
00:17:53,908 --> 00:17:54,593
what do we do?

296
00:17:54,595 --> 00:17:56,251
We take turns watching the baby, right?

297
00:17:56,268 --> 00:17:57,310
I'll watch the baby,

298
00:17:57,366 --> 00:18:00,602
see if I can talk to Daniel. You get some sleep. You look exhausted.

299
00:18:00,607 --> 00:18:01,502
All right.

300
00:18:01,847 --> 00:18:02,741
Good night.

301
00:18:04,555 --> 00:18:05,943
Hi! Hi!

302
00:18:07,885 --> 00:18:09,832
Don't cry. I'll just get you a bottle.

303
00:18:17,055 --> 00:18:18,451
You can trust me, you know.

304
00:18:19,876 --> 00:18:20,773
I won't hurt you.

305
00:18:22,487 --> 00:18:23,383
Melinda.

306
00:18:34,807 --> 00:18:38,701
<i>The itsy-bitsy spider went up the water spout</i>

307
00:18:39,225 --> 00:18:43,193
<i>down came the rain and washed the spider out</i>

308
00:18:43,906 --> 00:18:47,280
<i>up came the sun and dried up all the rain</i>

309
00:18:47,547 --> 00:18:51,710
<i>the itsy-bitsy spider went up the spout again.</i>

310
00:18:52,337 --> 00:18:53,631
That's a beautiful sight.

311
00:18:54,527 --> 00:18:55,772
Why aren't you sleeping?

312
00:18:56,006 --> 00:18:57,253
I gotta go to work soon.

313
00:18:58,827 --> 00:18:59,722
Here. Let me try.

314
00:19:10,236 --> 00:19:11,280
How you doing, girl?

315
00:19:12,526 --> 00:19:13,422
I'm impressed.

316
00:19:15,535 --> 00:19:16,432
Ok.

317
00:19:16,518 --> 00:19:17,411
There you are.

318
00:19:17,918 --> 00:19:19,203
Snug as a bug in a rug.

319
00:19:19,677 --> 00:19:20,572
Wow.

320
00:19:20,917 --> 00:19:22,312
Something my mom taught me.

321
00:19:25,037 --> 00:19:26,483
Makes you think, doesn't it?

322
00:19:26,628 --> 00:19:27,472
Sure.

323
00:19:27,476 --> 00:19:28,372
How can it not?

324
00:19:29,866 --> 00:19:31,810
You'd make a great mom, you know that?

325
00:19:32,636 --> 00:19:33,533
Whoa.

326
00:19:33,818 --> 00:19:34,713
We're not ready.

327
00:19:35,117 --> 00:19:38,262
- It's just not time yet.
- I know. I know we said we'd wait.

328
00:19:38,465 --> 00:19:39,361
I do. I just...

329
00:19:41,295 --> 00:19:43,441
sometimes I wonder what we're waiting for.

330
00:19:43,896 --> 00:19:45,541
A finished house, for one thing.

331
00:19:46,895 --> 00:19:48,362
We have so much to do.

332
00:19:48,716 --> 00:19:49,890
Work, save money.

333
00:19:50,346 --> 00:19:51,842
I'm taking every shift I can.

334
00:19:54,548 --> 00:19:56,141
You're really planning on this.

335
00:19:56,935 --> 00:19:58,180
I'm just thinking ahead.

336
00:19:58,907 --> 00:19:59,803
Well, it's...

337
00:20:00,358 --> 00:20:01,600
just not the right time.

338
00:20:04,715 --> 00:20:05,613
When?

339
00:20:05,916 --> 00:20:07,360
You can't put a clock on it.

340
00:20:07,725 --> 00:20:09,721
Your heart tells you when you're ready,

341
00:20:10,456 --> 00:20:11,602
not your bank account.

342
00:20:12,358 --> 00:20:13,550
I'm just not there yet.

343
00:20:19,428 --> 00:20:20,471
I better go to work.

344
00:20:24,207 --> 00:20:25,100
I'll call you.

345
00:20:52,307 --> 00:20:53,451
Please don't hurt her.

346
00:20:55,326 --> 00:20:56,520
No, you don't hurt her.

347
00:20:57,535 --> 00:20:59,881
I just wanna help you. Why are you still here?

348
00:21:01,865 --> 00:21:02,763
I live here.

349
00:21:03,565 --> 00:21:04,461
This is my home.

350
00:21:05,688 --> 00:21:07,781
But you don't live here anymore. I mean, don't you get it?

351
00:21:07,787 --> 00:21:09,782
You're mother's leaving because of you.

352
00:21:09,787 --> 00:21:10,933
You've driven her out.

353
00:21:11,138 --> 00:21:12,781
She was hardly ever here anyway.

354
00:21:16,436 --> 00:21:18,732
The job always came first for my mom and dad.

355
00:21:22,148 --> 00:21:23,791
Treated me like I was invisible.

356
00:21:29,076 --> 00:21:30,823
She always left me with the nanny.

357
00:21:37,478 --> 00:21:38,671
Lots of moms work hard.

358
00:21:39,266 --> 00:21:40,410
You just don't get it!

359
00:21:42,496 --> 00:21:43,392
Stop it!

360
00:21:43,548 --> 00:21:46,242
- You're scaring your sister.
- Just leave me alone!

361
00:21:47,115 --> 00:21:48,010
Daniel?

362
00:21:52,465 --> 00:21:53,363
Shh. Baby.

363
00:21:54,326 --> 00:21:55,221
It's ok.

364
00:22:14,927 --> 00:22:18,121
I know that it's hard to walk away from your mother and sister,

365
00:22:18,398 --> 00:22:20,191
but there's a better place for you.

366
00:22:20,568 --> 00:22:21,463
I'm not going.

367
00:22:22,278 --> 00:22:25,893
You're just hurting yourself and everyone around you. Is that what you really want?

368
00:22:25,898 --> 00:22:27,741
I'm not leaving until they find her.

369
00:22:28,315 --> 00:22:29,210
Who?

370
00:22:31,905 --> 00:22:32,800
Suzanne.

371
00:22:33,458 --> 00:22:34,353
Who is she?

372
00:22:35,358 --> 00:22:36,252
My nanny before.

373
00:22:38,458 --> 00:22:39,603
Is she special to you?

374
00:22:41,106 --> 00:22:42,000
Special.

375
00:22:52,856 --> 00:22:53,982
She watched me die.

376
00:23:10,436 --> 00:23:11,330
Melinda!

377
00:23:12,617 --> 00:23:14,130
- Melinda!
- I'm up here.

378
00:23:16,657 --> 00:23:19,471
- Oh, my god. I was so worried.
- That's ok. She's fine.

379
00:23:19,475 --> 00:23:21,872
She slept almost all the way through the night.

380
00:23:24,145 --> 00:23:25,042
How's Georgina?

381
00:23:25,345 --> 00:23:26,242
Ok.

382
00:23:26,797 --> 00:23:29,440
Nothing's broken. It's a miracle. Just some bruises.

383
00:23:30,856 --> 00:23:32,353
I guess that'll be a lawsuit.

384
00:23:34,937 --> 00:23:35,830
I'm sorry.

385
00:23:36,038 --> 00:23:37,932
You must think I'm hard or something.

386
00:23:38,135 --> 00:23:40,231
No.  I know that you have a lot of stress.

387
00:23:40,516 --> 00:23:42,862
It's just that work is really important to me.

388
00:23:43,275 --> 00:23:47,521
I want her to have everything that she needs, especially now that her father's gone.

389
00:23:47,717 --> 00:23:49,511
It's what I wanted for my son, too.

390
00:23:50,436 --> 00:23:53,180
Georgina told me that you lost your son. I'm so sorry.

391
00:23:54,777 --> 00:23:56,370
My husband and I, we were so...

392
00:23:57,615 --> 00:23:58,513
devastated.

393
00:23:59,155 --> 00:24:03,100
Just lost, you know. We couldn't figure out a plan. We didn't know what to do.

394
00:24:04,425 --> 00:24:07,821
I thought if we had another child it would give us a second chance.

395
00:24:08,135 --> 00:24:09,033
And it didn't.

396
00:24:10,736 --> 00:24:12,580
Ted just couldn't get back on track.

397
00:24:14,378 --> 00:24:15,270
I'm so sorry.

398
00:24:16,488 --> 00:24:19,461
Look, is there anything I can-- can I pay you for your time or...?

399
00:24:19,467 --> 00:24:22,113
No. No, I'm just really glad that it all worked out.

400
00:24:22,755 --> 00:24:24,452
There must be something I can do.

401
00:24:24,596 --> 00:24:25,490
Maybe one thing.

402
00:24:26,057 --> 00:24:28,302
You had a nanny before. Suzanne. Do you know

403
00:24:28,665 --> 00:24:29,812
how I might reach her?

404
00:24:30,946 --> 00:24:32,340
Who told you about Suzanne?

405
00:24:33,755 --> 00:24:35,542
Georgina... mentioned her.

406
00:24:36,407 --> 00:24:38,901
'Cause I have a friend who's looking for a nanny.

407
00:24:39,976 --> 00:24:43,273
Well, tell your friend to keep looking. She doesn't want Suzanne.

408
00:24:49,918 --> 00:24:52,541
You think Suzanne might be responsible for Daniel's death?

409
00:24:52,546 --> 00:24:54,541
I don't know, but either way, I have to find out.

410
00:24:54,545 --> 00:24:56,411
Because Daniel may be looking for revenge.

411
00:24:56,417 --> 00:24:59,211
- Man, he sounds like a little terror.
- Yeah, he's very troubled.

412
00:24:59,218 --> 00:25:01,800
I wish you'd called me last night. I would have been glad to come and help.

413
00:25:01,808 --> 00:25:03,831
Jim was there. Otherwise, I definitely would have.

414
00:25:03,838 --> 00:25:07,083
Ah! I get it. You were living out your dirty babysitter fantasy.

415
00:25:07,297 --> 00:25:10,692
Hardly. He saw me with the baby and started talking about having one of our own.

416
00:25:10,698 --> 00:25:13,652
- Oh! That's exciting.
- No, not really.

417
00:25:13,977 --> 00:25:17,571
Oh, come on, Melinda. Every time you see a baby, you're practically drooling.

418
00:25:17,575 --> 00:25:20,270
That does not mean I want to start a family tomorrow.

419
00:25:20,448 --> 00:25:21,213
Fine.

420
00:25:21,216 --> 00:25:23,371
Procreate at your own pace. See if I care.

421
00:25:23,748 --> 00:25:27,223
I'm sorry. I just hope that he doesn't start putting pressure on me about this.

422
00:25:27,226 --> 00:25:29,832
You know what? I totally get it. It's a huge responsibility.

423
00:25:29,837 --> 00:25:31,550
You shouldn't rush into it. He'll understand.

424
00:25:31,555 --> 00:25:33,550
- Oh! I found something!
- What is it?

425
00:25:33,888 --> 00:25:35,782
A newspaper report on Daniel's death.

426
00:25:36,166 --> 00:25:37,410
Does it say how he died?

427
00:25:37,435 --> 00:25:39,331
No. The police say it was accidental.

428
00:25:40,135 --> 00:25:42,311
But it does give me Suzanne's last name.

429
00:25:53,336 --> 00:25:54,232
Mr. Richards?

430
00:25:55,218 --> 00:25:55,982
Yeah?

431
00:25:55,987 --> 00:25:56,880
Is Suzanne here?

432
00:25:57,308 --> 00:25:58,201
Who's asking?

433
00:25:58,536 --> 00:26:01,583
Sorry. I'm Melinda Gordon. I'm a friend of Christine Greene.

434
00:26:02,417 --> 00:26:03,310
Oh, no.

435
00:26:03,915 --> 00:26:06,080
Please don't bring this whole thing up again.

436
00:26:06,085 --> 00:26:10,281
Do you have any idea how my wife's life was destroyed by what happened to that boy?

437
00:26:10,927 --> 00:26:12,272
I may be able to help her.

438
00:26:13,627 --> 00:26:14,523
How?

439
00:26:15,208 --> 00:26:17,451
Can you just tell me where I could find her?

440
00:26:31,317 --> 00:26:32,212
You've seen me.

441
00:26:32,826 --> 00:26:33,771
You gotta help me.

442
00:26:34,108 --> 00:26:36,541
Come on, lady. The jig is up. You looked me right in the eye.

443
00:26:36,548 --> 00:26:38,461
- Not now, ok?
- Yes. Please.

444
00:26:38,716 --> 00:26:41,692
I need to get a message to my wife. She's been living here for years.

445
00:26:41,696 --> 00:26:44,380
Do you have any idea how long I've been hanging around this place?

446
00:26:44,385 --> 00:26:45,282
It's depressing.

447
00:26:45,498 --> 00:26:48,131
The sheer monotony, not to mention the smell.

448
00:26:48,456 --> 00:26:50,701
Bleach and ammonia. I can't take it anymore.

449
00:26:55,505 --> 00:26:56,441
Oh, right.

450
00:26:56,685 --> 00:26:58,133
The kid gets your attention.

451
00:26:59,568 --> 00:27:00,940
- What am I, wood?
- You know what?

452
00:27:00,945 --> 00:27:03,191
I need you to help me find Suzanne Richards.

453
00:27:03,306 --> 00:27:04,401
Now you need my help?

454
00:27:04,496 --> 00:27:06,131
She's a caretaker, in her twenties.

455
00:27:06,137 --> 00:27:07,562
Are you gonna help me talk to my wife or not?

456
00:27:07,566 --> 00:27:10,761
If you help me find Suzanne, I will owe you one, ok? I promise.

457
00:27:11,365 --> 00:27:13,131
- I can't believe this.
- Please?

458
00:27:14,137 --> 00:27:15,830
She works up on the second floor.

459
00:27:15,926 --> 00:27:17,971
She was just up there changing the beds.

460
00:27:22,387 --> 00:27:23,280
Yes!

461
00:27:33,738 --> 00:27:34,633
Hi.

462
00:27:34,948 --> 00:27:36,643
- Who are you?
- Melinda Gordon.

463
00:27:37,338 --> 00:27:39,632
- Are you ok?
- Yeah, I think so.

464
00:27:40,567 --> 00:27:42,210
I just don't know what happened.

465
00:27:43,138 --> 00:27:44,690
I'm--I'm sorry. Who are you?

466
00:27:45,255 --> 00:27:46,521
You're Suzanne, right?

467
00:27:47,358 --> 00:27:49,100
I'm a friend of the Greene family.

468
00:27:49,888 --> 00:27:50,782
Oh.

469
00:27:51,185 --> 00:27:53,181
And I want to talk to you about Daniel.

470
00:27:54,025 --> 00:27:57,221
I'm sorry. I don't know what you want, but I don't talk about Daniel.

471
00:27:57,235 --> 00:27:58,530
Well, he talks about you.

472
00:27:59,326 --> 00:28:01,243
- Daniel's dead.
- Daniel's here.

473
00:28:01,757 --> 00:28:02,850
Who the hell are you?

474
00:28:03,996 --> 00:28:05,991
Just a person who's trying to help you.

475
00:28:06,886 --> 00:28:10,033
Look, I know that this is hard to believe, but Daniel's here--

476
00:28:10,067 --> 00:28:14,012
his spirit anyway-- and he told me that he won't cross over until he sees you.

477
00:28:16,636 --> 00:28:18,683
- I'm calling security.
- Please don't.

478
00:28:19,898 --> 00:28:22,523
Just give me 5 minutes. You may be in danger.

479
00:28:23,105 --> 00:28:25,051
She's wearing the bracelet I made her.

480
00:28:26,686 --> 00:28:28,132
This is the one she made me.

481
00:28:33,416 --> 00:28:36,111
He says that you're wearing the bracelet he made you,

482
00:28:36,587 --> 00:28:38,782
and he's wearing the one that you made him.

483
00:28:41,346 --> 00:28:42,341
I don't understand.

484
00:28:44,487 --> 00:28:46,932
Ask her if she remembers what happened that day.

485
00:28:47,718 --> 00:28:50,913
He wants to know if you remember what happened the day he died.

486
00:28:52,188 --> 00:28:54,480
Do I remember? What kind of question is that?

487
00:28:54,916 --> 00:28:56,011
I'll always remember.

488
00:28:56,515 --> 00:28:57,761
He wants you to tell me.

489
00:29:04,456 --> 00:29:06,101
I only know what happened after.

490
00:29:06,566 --> 00:29:07,460
After what?

491
00:29:08,767 --> 00:29:10,980
After he went upstairs to see Christine.

492
00:29:12,967 --> 00:29:14,413
It was saturday, my day off,

493
00:29:15,527 --> 00:29:18,721
but Christine had asked me to do some household chores for her.

494
00:29:19,296 --> 00:29:20,791
I heard Daniel. He was upset.

495
00:29:21,328 --> 00:29:22,923
He was running down the stairs.

496
00:29:24,937 --> 00:29:25,833
Daniel?

497
00:29:33,836 --> 00:29:34,730
Daniel!

498
00:29:38,677 --> 00:29:40,540
Daniel! Stop! What are you doing?!

499
00:29:45,935 --> 00:29:46,831
Daniel!

500
00:29:49,777 --> 00:29:51,870
By the time I got there, it was too late.

501
00:29:56,575 --> 00:29:57,472
I saw him die.

502
00:29:59,965 --> 00:30:02,210
He died right in front of me, looking at me.

503
00:30:03,247 --> 00:30:04,742
He said his last words to me.

504
00:30:08,056 --> 00:30:09,001
And then Christine

505
00:30:09,578 --> 00:30:10,922
was right there behind me.

506
00:30:33,808 --> 00:30:35,290
Somebody please help us!

507
00:30:38,898 --> 00:30:40,841
It was all over in less than a minute.

508
00:30:44,435 --> 00:30:47,361
But I can't get the image of that car out of my head,

509
00:30:50,068 --> 00:30:52,811
of his face, of Christine's face.

510
00:30:57,556 --> 00:30:59,003
Sometimes I wake up thinking

511
00:30:59,847 --> 00:31:02,990
I should have stopped him somehow. There must have been a way.

512
00:31:03,858 --> 00:31:05,673
Maybe if I would have been quicker.

513
00:31:09,557 --> 00:31:11,142
My mother thought that Suzanne

514
00:31:12,225 --> 00:31:14,123
could have done something to stop me,

515
00:31:15,198 --> 00:31:16,090
but she's wrong.

516
00:31:20,697 --> 00:31:22,340
She couldn't have done anything.

517
00:31:27,398 --> 00:31:29,242
I never meant for her to get blamed.

518
00:31:31,515 --> 00:31:33,710
She's the only person that took care of me,

519
00:31:34,245 --> 00:31:35,293
the only person that

520
00:31:35,836 --> 00:31:37,100
really cared, you know.

521
00:31:40,707 --> 00:31:41,652
She made me laugh.

522
00:31:43,525 --> 00:31:45,921
Sit with me for hours and play with the trains.

523
00:31:48,167 --> 00:31:49,040
What?

524
00:31:49,045 --> 00:31:51,190
- What's happening in here?
- One second.

525
00:31:51,405 --> 00:31:55,152
